    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>5 Aboard a U.S. Helicopter Die in a Crash in El Salvador</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>SAN SALVADOR, Feb. 25</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A United States Army helicopter crashed in Lake Ilopango east of San Salvador today, killing the five soldiers aboard, officials said. The pilot of the UH-1H had reported mechanical trouble minutes after taking off from the Salvadoran Air Force headquarters at Ilopango, a United States Embassy spokesman said.</p>
        <p>Aboard were four Army crewmen based at Soto Cano Air Base in Honduras and one of 55 American military personnel who train and advise the Salvadoran military, the spokesman, Jeff Brown, said. Their names were withheld pending notification of relatives.</p>
      </block>
